{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is parser/resolver handoff: direct+transitive extraction then passing the full set into the vulnerability-check module. A single-function unit test can miss dropped transitive deps at module boundaries (MOCK-MISS). No real OS/network/subprocess is required by the behavior text, and no AI output is involved, so System/Agentic/Workflow are disqualified.","test_description":"Run scanner modules together on fixture manifests/lockfiles containing nested transitive dependencies; assert the vulnerability-check input set contains every expected direct and transitive package/version entry.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly targets correctness of database query matching against exact version ranges, which is an external API contract. Stubbed responses can hide real failures where request encoding/semver-range semantics differ from the real service (REAL-INFRA, MOCK-HIDE). Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because this is not model judgment or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Against a real vulnerability DB endpoint (or provider sandbox), issue queries generated from manifests with overlapping package names but different version ranges; assert returned CVEs correspond only to the exact declared ranges.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic ordering logic within one algorithmic boundary; no module interaction or infrastructure is required. Rejection gate: Integration/System/Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by the behavior text, which only specifies sort order rules.","test_description":"Pass an unsorted in-memory CVE list spanning all severities and tied severities with different CVSS values; assert exact output order by severity rank then descending CVSS.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is typically in parse->mutate->serialize wiring (e.g., unintended edits/reordering), not just a pure setter function. In-process integration across manifest reader/updater/writer catches this. Rejection gate: System is disqualified because behavior text does not require real OS/network/subprocess effects; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified (no AI).","test_description":"Run manifest load/update/save pipeline on realistic manifest fixtures; diff before/after and assert exactly one dependency version change with all other keys/values untouched.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires creation on the real repository, which crosses real VCS hosting/network/API boundaries (REAL-INFRA). Mocks can pass while auth, branch, diff, or PR API behavior fails in reality (MOCK-HIDE). Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no model-dependent decision quality is specified.","test_description":"Execute scanner against a real test repository and verify an actual PR is opened; assert PR diff contains exactly one dependency version bump and no unrelated file changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.92,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Semver major-bump detection is local deterministic logic; one function/object boundary suffices. Rejection gate: higher levels are disqualified because behavior text is strictly comparison logic, with no external infra or model output.","test_description":"Feed version pairs covering major/minor/patch/pre-release edge cases into semver comparator; assert only major increments are flagged as breaking.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration/state handoff: semver decision must suppress PR module invocation and propagate a review flag to output. A unit test of either module alone can miss the cross-module control-flow failure (MOCK-MISS). Integration-brake checks: no required real OS/network if PR client is in-process fake and assertion is 'not called'; no AI; no multi-agent chain.","test_description":"Wire scanner decision engine, PR trigger component, and reporting component in-process; simulate a breaking bump and assert PR creation path is not invoked while output contains the